#landing
ssttp.landing.title = Set up a Self Assessment payment plan

ssttp.landing.p1 = A payment plan allows you to pay your tax charges in instalments over a period of time.
ssttp.landing.p2 = Your plan covers the tax you owe and, if applicable, the 2 advance payments towards your tax bill. It also covers any penalties or charges against your account. You’ll have to pay interest on the amount you pay late.
ssttp.landing.p3 = To be eligible to set up an online payment plan you need to:
ssttp.landing.p3list.1 = ensure your tax returns are up to date
ssttp.landing.p3list.2 = owe £{0} or less
ssttp.landing.p3list.3 = have no other tax debts
ssttp.landing.p3list.4 = have no other HMRC payment plans set up
ssttp.landing.p4 = You can use this service within 60 days of the payment deadline.

ssttp.landing.start-button.label = Start now

ssttp.landing.before-you-start = Before you start
ssttp.landing.before-you-start.p1 = HMRC intend this as a one-off payment plan to give you extra support. You must keep up to date with your payments. If you do not, HMRC may ask you to pay the entire outstanding amount.
ssttp.landing.before-you-start.p2 = To set up the payment plan, you’ll need to know your monthly income and spending, and any savings or investments.


#affordability

ssttp.affordability.start.h1 = We need to check you can afford the payment plan
ssttp.affordability.start.p1 = To make sure you can afford your payment plan for the remaining <strong>{0}</strong>, we need to ask about your income and spending. We will use this information to check how much income you have left over after your essential monthly spending.
ssttp.affordability.start.p2 = You may need to look at bank statements or utility bills before you continue. HMRC may ask for proof of your income and spending.
ssttp.affordability.start.p3 = If you decide to call us, we will still ask you about your income and spending.
ssttp.affordability.start.detail = How we calculate the plan
ssttp.affordability.start.detail.text1 = We expect you to pay around half of your left over income towards the tax you owe. This is to help you:
ssttp.affordability.start.detail.list1 = afford your monthly payments
ssttp.affordability.start.detail.list2 = manage any unexpected changes in spending
ssttp.affordability.start.detail.text2 = You can choose to pay more than half of your left over income. This will reduce the interest you pay.


