#accessibilitystatement
 accessibility-statement.title = Accessibility Statement
 accessibility-statement.link = Accessibility statement
 accessibility-statement-h1 = Accessibility statement for set up a Self Assessment payment plan
 accessibility-statement-p1 = This accessibility statement explains how accessible this service is, what to do if you have difficulty using it and how to report accessibility problems with the service.
 accessibility-statement-p2a = This service is part of the wider GOV.UK website. There is a separate
 accessibility-statement-a1 =  accessibility statement
 accessibility-statement-p2b = for the main GOV.UK website.
 accessibility-statement-p3a = This statement only contains information about
 accessibility-statement-p3b = this service
 accessibility-statement-h2 = Using this service
 accessibility-statement-p4 = This service allows you to set up a payment plan to pay overdue Self Assessment tax charges in instalments, if you are eligible.
 accessibility-statement-p5 = This service is run by HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC). We want as many people as possible to be able to use this service. This means you should be able to:
 accessibility-statement.l1.item1 = change colours, contrast levels and fonts
 accessibility-statement.l1.item2 = zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen
 accessibility-statement.l1.item3 = get from the start of the service to the end using just a keyboard
 accessibility-statement.l1.item4 = get from the start of the service to the end using speech recognition software
 accessibility-statement.l1.item5 = listen to the service using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver)
 accessibility-statement-p6 = We have also made the text in the service as simple as possible to understand.
 accessibility-statement-welsh-addition-1 =
 accessibility-statement-a2 = AbilityNet
 accessibility-statement-p7 = has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability.
 accessibility-statement-h3 = How accessible this service is
 accessibility-statement-p8 = This service is partially compliant with the
 accessibility-statement-a3 = Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1 AA standard
 accessibility-statement-p9 = Some people may find parts of this service difficult to use:
 accessibility-statement.l2.item1 = some error messages are not descriptive enough for people with visual impairments - but are compatible with common assistive technology tools
 accessibility-statement.l2.item2 = some headings are not consistent
 accessibility-statement.l2.item3 = elements which are missing their labels - using a screen reader to read back the entire page will provide all the information needed
 accessibility-statement-h4 = Reporting accessibility problems with this service
 accessibility-statement-p10 = We are always looking to improve the accessibility of this service. If you find any problems that are not listed on this page or think we are not meeting accessibility requirements, report the
 accessibility-statement-a4 = accessibility problem (opens in a new tab)
 accessibility-statement-h5 = What to do if you are not happy with how we respond to your complaint
 accessibility-statement-p11a = The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the ‘accessibility regulations’). If you are not happy with how we respond to your complaint,
 accessibility-statement-a5 = contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS)
 accessibility-statement-p11b = , or the
 accessibility-statement-a6 = Equality Commission for Northern Ireland (ECNI)
 accessibility-statement-p11c = if you live in Northern Ireland.
 accessibility-statement-h6 = Contacting us by phone or getting a visit from us in person
 accessibility-statement-p12 = We provide a text relay service if you are deaf, hearing impaired or have a speech impediment.
 accessibility-statement-p13 = We can provide a British Sign Language (BSL) interpreter, or you can arrange a visit from an HMRC advisor to help you complete the service.
 accessibility-statement-p14 = Find out how to
 accessibility-statement-a7 = contact us
 accessibility-statement-h7 = Technical information about this service’s accessibility
 accessibility-statement-p15 = HMRC is committed to making this service accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.
 accessibility-statement-p16a = This service is partially compliant with the
 accessibility-statement-a8 = Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1 AA standard
 accessibility-statement-p16b = , due to the non-compliances listed below.
 accessibility-statement-h8 = Non-accessible content
 accessibility-statement-p17 = The content listed below is non-accessible for the following reasons.
 accessibility-statement-h9 = Non-compliance with the accessibility regulations
 accessibility-statement-p18 = This service uses radio buttons which are grouped so that the page can be navigated with only the keyboard.
 accessibility-statement-p19 = In some places, these groups are missing their labels which means screen reading software will not read out the description of the selected element. This does not meet WCAG success criterion 2.4.6 (Headings and Labels).
 accessibility-statement-p20 = We plan to add the correct labels and field sets to all of our radio buttons by 15 December 2021.
 accessibility-statement-p21 = We use tab titles to describe the content of our web pages. In some places, the tab titles do not match the heading of the page. This does not meet WCAG 2.1 success criterion 2.4.6 (Headings and Labels).
 accessibility-statement-p22 = We plan to add consistent titles and headings for all the pages in the service by 15 December 2021.
 accessibility-statement-p23 = Some error messages are not descriptive enough for people with visual impairments. This does not meet WCAG Success Criterion 3.3.3 (Error Suggestion)
 accessibility-statement-p24 = The service is not fully compliant with WCAG 2.2.1 (timing adjustable) as there is not a warning for the service timeout.
 accessibility-statement-p25 = We plan to meet this criterion by 15 December 2021.
 accessibility-statement-h10 = How we tested this service
 accessibility-statement-p26 = The service was last tested on 14 February 2019 and was checked for compliance with WCAG 2.1 AA.
 accessibility-statement-p27a = The service was built using parts that were tested by the
 accessibility-statement-a9 = Digital Accessibility Centre
 accessibility-statement-p27b = . The full service was tested by HMRC and included disabled users.
 accessibility-statement-p28 = This page was prepared on 26 February 2020. It was last updated on 11 February 2021.

